commit.message:
Merge pull request #37 from jleclanche/fix/33

Use relative imports. Fixes #33
Use relative imports. Fixes #33
bump version to 0.0.2

Merge pull request #29 from jreese/groupby

Support multiple fields in --group-by
Fix checking file exist even for 'stdin' log.

Support multiple fields in --group-by

This allows --group-by to take a comma-separated list of field names,
and processes the field list before passing it to the SQLProcessor. When
displaying the results, it displays as two separate fields.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/mcortizo/ngxtop into mcortizo-master

Allow ngxtop to parse logs directly from stdin. Pre-defined common log format for Apache access log.
Update README
Remove -s option, as it is not really needed
Better parsing of nginx config file for access_log and log_format directives with pyparsing. Properly handle multiple access logs.
Improve detection of stdin input and add example, add 'common' format constant, add available variables for filters to doc
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/lebinh/ngxtop
Use curses instead of repeatedly clear terminal screen and switch to timer signal for periodically printing of report instead of threads.
Added option for database dump
Enable input from stdin, such as pipe output
Remove .py extension in examples
Add blank line after literal block so restructuredtext won't complain.
Add pypi package and installation info in readme.
Change default log location to '/var/log/nginx/access.log' as it's the default in Debian / Ubuntu.
add support for python3
Restructured and prepared for packaging

Fix spelling mistake

Fixed typo.
